    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Contrary to Popular Belief, "EQ: SoL" actually stands for "EverQuest: Shadows of Luclin"</b></font>
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>GeneralNews
        [ 11:46 PM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">
        <a href="mailto:thundolfe@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Thundolfe</a></font>
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> There's a lot of information coming out of E3 about <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/luclin/">EverQuest: The Shadows of Luclin</a>. Here's a rundown of sites and such with information:<br><br><ul><br><li><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com">Castersrealm</a> has an <a href="http://e3.crgaming.com">interview with Jeff Butler</a> regarding the upcoming changes in SoL.<br><br><li><a href="http://www.lumthemad.net/">Lum the Mad</a> also has some information of Luclin, as well as a bunch of information on some of the <a href="http://camelot.stratics.com">newer</a> <a href="http://sb.stratics.com">games</a> coming out. One of which you've <a href="http://www.starwarsgalaxies.com/">NEVER HEARD OF</a>. I bet.<br><br><li>Last but certainly not least <b>Svengali</b> from our <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/content/forums/westwood.html">Westwood Tavern</a> is attending E3 and saw a good bit of Luclin. Here's a snippet of his <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/php-bin/eq/showflat.php?Cat=&Board=eqwestwood&Number=534095&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5&o=7&part=">impressions</a>:<br><blockquote>The new player models looked absolutely awesome. They had human, kerran, and (my favorite) troll up and going. (I think the others are still in the works, but didn't bother to ask. I was told, point blank, that he could pull up only those three.) I saw some NPC gnomes, so those _might_ be the new gnome looks, but that's neither here nor there. The plan is that when you buy Luclin you get to decide whether to see the updated player models or the older player models. If you choose the updated models, you get to pick re-pick what you look like. I still had a ton of questions at this point, but they got washed away. What I thought important was that you will get to decide between the old and the new and also get to pick your specific new look.</blockquote><br>You can read his full commentary and add your own comments <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/php-bin/eq/showflat.php?Cat=&Board=eqwestwood&Number=534095&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5&o=7&part=">here</a>.<br></ul><br><br>By the way, yes, I know what else "SOL" stands for. YOU CAN STOP EMAILING ME ABOUT IT NOW. THANKS.<br><br>More coming soon, stay tuned! </font>
